item.title: CVE-2018-1124|2024-08-05T03:51:48.632Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- procps-ng
item.description: procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to multiple integer overflows leading to a heap corruption in file2strvec function. This allows a privilege escalation for a local attacker who can create entries in procfs by starting processes, which could result in crashes or arbitrary code execution in proc utilities run by other users.
